docs.abstract: Election fraud is exceedingly rare and often accidental. Still, G.O.P. lawmakers and prosecutors are promoting tough new enforcement efforts.
docs.snippet: Election fraud is exceedingly rare and often accidental. Still, G.O.P. lawmakers and prosecutors are promoting tough new enforcement efforts.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Florida Legislature last week created a law enforcement agency — informally called the election police — to tackle what Gov. Ron DeSantis and other Republicans have declared an urgent problem: the roughly 0.000677 percent of voters suspected of committing voter fraud.

headline.main: Republicans Push Crackdown on Crime Wave That Doesn’t Exist: Voter Fraud

docs.abstract: The actor is directing an Encores! revival of the 1997 musical, updating it to confront hard truths about racism, poverty and carceral injustice.
docs.snippet: The actor is directing an Encores! revival of the 1997 musical, updating it to confront hard truths about racism, poverty and carceral injustice.
docs.lead_paragraph: When “The Life” opened on Broadway in 1997, the sex trade in Times Square that it depicts was no longer a prominent feature of the area. Like an increasingly polished Midtown Manhattan, the musical, about the women and men who once made it a prostitution capital, was sufficiently family-friendly for my parents to take me to see it, at the age of 15, as my first Broadway show.

headline.main: Comedy Undercut ‘The Life.’ Billy Porter Looks for Its Humanity.

docs.lead_paragraph: Dressed in an indelible red coat, Elizabeth Alexander stood aloft the National Mall and faced a sea of expectant faces. Behind her, a platform seated rows upon rows of eminences, including President Barack Obama. In her inaugural poem Alexander likened love to light and closed with lines that bespoke the optimism of the occasion: “On the brink, on the brim, on the cusp,/praise song for walking forward in that light.”

headline.main: In the Face of Black Pain, Elizabeth Alexander Turns to Art

docs.abstract: How a themed gathering at a basketball game revealed racial fault lines in a rural New York town.
docs.snippet: How a themed gathering at a basketball game revealed racial fault lines in a rural New York town.
docs.lead_paragraph: Windsor, N.Y., population 833, is described by residents on Facebook as “that nice rustic town on the Susquehanna River.” Located in the state’s Southern Tier close to the Pennsylvania border, it offers vistas of farmland, dotted with several big clapboard houses painted a duck-egg blue. The closest city is Binghamton, 16 miles away.

headline.main: Students Planned a ‘Gangsta Night’ Event. Some Thought It Was Racist.
headline.print_headline: Students Held a ‘Gangsta Night.’  Some People Saw It as Racist.

docs.abstract: The trip by Prince William and his wife, Catherine, the duchess of Cambridge, dramatized how rapidly Queen Elizabeth II is losing her grip on distant dominions where she is still head of state.
docs.snippet: The trip by Prince William and his wife, Catherine, the duchess of Cambridge, dramatized how rapidly Queen Elizabeth II is losing her grip on distant dominions where she is still head of state.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — In Belize, a visit to a cocoa farm was scotched after residents protested. In Jamaica, the prime minister declared his country was “moving on” from the British monarchy. In the Bahamas, the couple arrived to demands from a group calling for slavery reparations that they acknowledge Britain’s economy “was built on the backs of our ancestors.”

headline.main: Gaffes and Miscues Mar a Royal Tour of a Republic-Minded Caribbean
headline.print_headline: Caribbean Nations Show New Attitude While Hosting British Royals

docs.abstract: Even after his father was murdered, he opposed capital punishment and led the effort to repeal it in New Hampshire. Three decades later, he succeeded.
docs.snippet: Even after his father was murdered, he opposed capital punishment and led the effort to repeal it in New Hampshire. Three decades later, he succeeded.
docs.lead_paragraph: Robert R. Cushing Sr., a retired elementary-school teacher, was watching a basketball game on television at his home in New Hampshire in 1988 when he heard a knock at the door. When he answered it, a man fired two blasts from a sawed-off shotgun, killing him in front of his wife, and fled.

headline.main: Renny Cushing, Relentless Foe of Death Penalty, Dies at 69

docs.abstract: A federal grand jury charged Enrique Tarrio with conspiracy in the Capitol attack last year, making him the second leader of a far-right group to face charges in the past several months.
docs.snippet: A federal grand jury charged Enrique Tarrio with conspiracy in the Capitol attack last year, making him the second leader of a far-right group to face charges in the past several months.
docs.lead_paragraph: Enrique Tarrio, the former leader of the Proud Boys, was charged in a federal indictment unsealed on Tuesday with conspiring with other top lieutenants of the far-right nationalist group to disrupt the certification of the 2020 presidential election by helping to plan and launch the attack on the Capitol last year.

headline.main: Former Proud Boys Leader Indicted in Jan. 6 Investigation

docs.abstract: As teams snatch up quarterbacks in free agency, Kaepernick has been quickly organizing workouts around the country and posting them to social media.
docs.snippet: As teams snatch up quarterbacks in free agency, Kaepernick has been quickly organizing workouts around the country and posting them to social media.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — In the five years since he last played in an N.F.L. game, Colin Kaepernick, the former San Francisco 49ers quarterback who ignited an international debate on athletes’ right to protest, has only sporadically surfaced in public. Accepting an award here, or rolling out a Netflix series there, Kaepernick has in those calculated appearances always affirmed that he was “staying ready” for a return to football.

headline.main: Colin Kaepernick Campaigns for N.F.L. Return With Pop-Up Workouts
headline.print_headline: Kaepernick Stages His Own Pop-Up Auditions
